Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the wedges cook, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the onion and stir-fry until soft and golden, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, finely chop the @dried cranberries{30%g}(finely chopped). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}(grated).

In a large #bowl, combine the @British pork and oregano sausage meat{225%g}, chopped cranberries and half the cooked onion.

Put the remaining onion into a small bowl and set aside for later.

Season the sausage meat with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix together with your hands.

Roll the mixture into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Pop the burgers onto another baking tray and lay the @British streaky bacon{4%slices} in a single layer alongside.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the burgers are cooked through and the bacon is golden brown and crispy, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Meanwhile, halve the @glazed burger bun{2}(halved).

When the burgers and bacon are cooked, remove the tray from the oven and put the bacon aside on a #plate lined with kitchen paper. Top each burger with the remaining onion, then the grated cheese.

Place the buns onto same tray and pop back into the oven until the cheese has melted and the buns are warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, pop the buns on your plates and spread the @apple and sage jelly{25%g} over the bases, then top with the sausage burgers, crispy bacon (two rashers each), @wild rocket{20%g} and bun lids.

Serve with the wedges alongside.

Enjoy!